&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;u&gt;Everyone says they want to change the world. We&#39;re looking for people who actually will.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;em&gt;ADF International is a faith-based legal advocacy organization that protects fundamental freedoms and promotes the inherent dignity of all people. Please visit our&amp;nbsp;&lt;a href=&quot;http://adfinternational.org/about-us/careers&quot;&gt;career site&lt;/a&gt; to view our Statement of Faith and&amp;nbsp;Doctrinal Distinctives.&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Location:&amp;nbsp;&lt;/strong&gt;London, England&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Team Overview:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;As the Director, Human Resources, you are a vital part of ADF International’s Senior Leadership Team. Based in London and reporting to the Vice President of Human Resources at ADF, you will serve as the primary architect of all people strategies, policies, and programs across the organization. This is a strategic, hands-on leadership role responsible for building and stewarding a high-performing, values-aligned workforce capable of fulfilling ADF International’s global mission. The role is ideally suited for a seasoned HR professional who understands the unique culture and operational context of a mission-driven, international organization and who is passionate about empowering people to do their best work in service of a larger cause.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Key Responsibilities:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Strategic HR Leadership&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Partner with the VP of Human Resources to develop and execute a shared services people strategy aligned with ADFI&#39;s mission, values, and long-term goals&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Drive organizational design and workforce planning across global offices&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Team Leadership &amp;amp; Supervision&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Lead and develop a small HR team (HR Manager &amp;amp; HR Coordinator) by building a collaborative and high-performing culture&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Set objectives and performance expectations for direct reports through regular one-to-ones and formal reviews, supporting their growth and career progression&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Allocate work for appropriate coverage, model ADFI&#39;s values, and act as the escalation point for complex or sensitive HR matters&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Employee Relations &amp;amp; Culture&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Serve as the primary contact for employee relations, giving fair, consistent, legally compliant guidance and handling sensitive matters with discretion and pastoral care&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Champion a mission-rooted culture and run programs supporting wellbeing, resilience, and work-life integration across a globally dispersed team&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Performance &amp;amp; Development&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Collaborate with Talent Development leaders to manage a performance framework that drives excellence, accountability, and growth&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Identify learning needs and partner with managers on training, succession planning, and retention of high-potential staff&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Collaborate with Centers of Excellence&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Collaborate with Talent Acquisition and Total Rewards Center of Excellence teams&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Maintain HR records and HRIS, and prepare reporting and analytics on headcount, turnover, engagement, and other key metrics&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;International HR Coordination&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Provide HR support and policy guidance across international offices, adapting global frameworks to local legal and cultural contexts&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Serve as lead resource on international HR projects and Initiatives&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Minimum Qualifications:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Fluent in English&lt;/li&g

&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;u&gt;Everyone says they want to change the world. We&#39;re looking for people who actually will.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;em&gt;ADF International is a faith-based legal advocacy organization that protects fundamental freedoms and promotes the inherent dignity of all people. Please visit our&amp;nbsp;&lt;a href=&quot;http://adfinternational.org/about-us/careers&quot;&gt;career site&lt;/a&gt;&amp;nbsp;to view our Statement of Faith and&amp;nbsp;Doctrinal Distinctives.&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Director of Advocacy, UK &amp;amp; Commonwealth&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This position requires at least 2 years of experience managing or leading a small legal team.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;ADF International is looking for a &lt;strong&gt;Director of Advocacy, UK &amp;amp; Commonwealth,&amp;nbsp;&lt;/strong&gt;to join us full-time in our London, UK office. As the Director of Advocacy, UK &amp;amp; Commonwealth, you are a vital part of ADF International. In this role, you will report to the Director of Advocacy and lead the UK &amp;amp; Commonwealth Advocacy Team, based in the London office. You are responsible for leading the advocacy strategy for the UK and Commonwealth without substantial oversight. You will work with and through your team to engage in legal advocacy, litigation, and public advocacy before law-making bodies to set the strongest precedents in pursuit of our mission. You will develop legal strategies, draft legal documents and work with allies and other stakeholders in a range of settings. You will work closely with our communications and development teams to ensure the success of our advocacy.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Your Essential Responsibilities:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;In this position you will:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ol&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Lead, manage, recruit, and develop the UK &amp;amp; Commonwealth advocacy team to achieve ADF International objectives.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Serve as part of the senior legal team of ADF International.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Engage in legal advocacy in pursuit of ADF International objectives:
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Develop and implement strategies in pursuit of agreed generational wins in the UK.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Lead, join, or assist in efforts to establish positive precedents and laws at the highest available courts and law-making institutions.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Cultivate a network of meaningful relationships with key stakeholders including lawyers, parliamentarians, advisors, and civil servants.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Identify, mobilize, and train others in support of the ADF International mission:
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Provide training on ADF International issues both internally and externally.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Work to identify and recommend for training candidates of the highest caliber.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Engage with the media, thought leaders, academics, and other audiences by:
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Completing media interviews and acting as a spokesperson for ADF International.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Researching and publishing short and extended pieces in support of ADF International objectives.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Cooperate with the Development team as required in support of fundraising efforts.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ol&gt;
&lt;p&gt;As a Team Leader, you will:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Act as a servant leader by training, encouraging, coaching, and developing your Team Members.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Foster a spirit of trust and of innovation on your team.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Meet regularly with your Direct Reports to discuss their progress and complete performance reviews.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Approve PTO requests, time cards, and expense reports.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
